{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eadca8e5-33d8-42db-8e60-c80010819bcc","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the new platform** by adding this property:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained executables):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (2.9.3+) — only the *runner* changes.\n- The `xunit.runner.mtp` package replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- No code changes needed in your tests.\n- You gain direct-exe execution, better parallelism options, and the new `--` CLI flags.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0c9f952d-c405-4909-8672-06bc607add6b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"BD16:3113E4:1D546E2:20FE623:6A07C429"},"id":"56e32cdc-3d83-41de-8d6b-bceda9edf4c2","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:11:15.661Z","parentId":"9301651c-c0b7-4096-b4bc-c9ab066a90dd"}
